{
  "doc_id": "22536",
  "text": "In vitro models are also very useful for determining the intrinsic clearance of compounds. Examples of such in vitro models are microsomes, isolated hepatocytes, and liver slices. A drawback of these models is the time limit imposed on experiments. Enzyme activities drop within a few hours, and in slices and hepatocytes, cell death is observed in less than 6 h [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Even though many successful predictions about kinetics have been made for several compounds, in vitro clearance is still hard to predict for compounds with a low extraction ratio [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
